{
  "stem": "10406.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was walking, and most of the older people wore these long coats, you know?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And by chance, a sled with two German officers was coming right opposite to where he was walking, and when they saw him-- and, of course he was an old man and had a beard and payots, you know-- they stopped.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They stopped, and one of them got off.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was maybe, like, a half a block away, and he was probably saying things to him.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Like they normally would insult Jews-- [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Suddenly-- suddenly, he pushed him into the snow, and the old man fell.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And his hat fell off.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he made him put snow into the hat and put it on him, and abused him some more.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The other officer was saying already, come on, let's go, like, that's enough, you know.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he got back on the sled and they continued.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That was the direction of the headquarters.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the old man got himself up and cleaned out his hat and went home.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It so happens later on towards the end when they kill everybody, I end up hiding in a hiding place in this man's home, and I was there when they captured everybody, and I managed to get away.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then another thing I saw was this-- another incident happened before that where one of the Germans that was patrolling at night somehow had an encounter towards late evening, after the curfew, with the only photographer in town.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We had a photographer who probably took all those pictures that I have from our town-- was taken by him because there was only one photographer with a studio that did all this stuff.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And there was some argument between this German soldier.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Now, he was not an SS.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He was still-- there was a-- there was a group of soldiers stationed also in town to do certain things, and I can see why because the SS were busy doing, you know, what they thought important things-- killing people and so on.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Massacring.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that soldier was drunk, and he ran into some misunderstanding with the photographer and stabbed him to death.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "From what I understand, that particular commandant or the head of that military group in town, who was an older German, possibly of Austrian background and was there during the First World War, the Austro-Hungary empire.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was captured as prisoner and was stationed in our town for some reason, as prisoner he was there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the Jews of the town somehow helped him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They gave him food and gave him-- so he sort of-- that soldier was punished, the one that stabbed the man.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that was the first killing in town.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And whether it's true or not-- I hardly believe that that would be true-- that soldier was executed.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I have my doubts whether they would actually kill him, but that's possible.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, but this was seen by people that I spoke-- yeah, that was a fact.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, you began to feel that, you know, any German can go into any-- which they could at that point-- to any Jewish home and basically do what they wanted to.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The next thing I saw was we had not many, like, real Hasidim that would wear the fur hats like the very Hasidic people do.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In our town, only the rabbi wore a hat like that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But there was somebody married, a person like that, who lived in the town.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was a young man.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he-- again, it was his luck to walk on my street, like, one house away.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And suddenly I saw this German soldier with his rifle butt, you know, hitting that man over the head.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the man collapsed, cursing at him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And eventually the soldier left, and he managed to get up.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he only lived, like, a block away.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I saw the way he was walking, like, he was having trouble.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He made it back to his house, and he died the next day.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it just didn't happen suddenly.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So now, you know, it's a process.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The next thing that happens is that we-- somehow we get the feeling that something is going to happen.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that was-- that was in the beginning of '42.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so at that point, we thought it was serious, so my mother, my sister, my brother, and I went to our grandparents' house, my father's parents' house, and they made a hiding place.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was on-- it was on one of the streets going from-- from [POLISH] to [POLISH], and it was, like, a little bit out of the city already.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was, like, in a suburb area.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were probably the only Jewish house at that particular spot.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
